main event: Several witnesses reported seeing an elongated object moving rapidly northward in South Berwick, Maine on May 6, 1969.
interesting points: The object was observed for 10-15 minutes during the evening hours.
The object appeared to be around 50-60 feet long.
The witnesses could not see the object any longer after it flashed brightly.
The object was reported to change direction and height before disappearing and reappearing.
The witnesses described the object as having a fluttering or wobbling motion.
